HEADWORD: Cellarage
<hw>Cel"lar*age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
space or storerooms of a cellar; a cellar.</def> <rj><au>Sir W.
Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You hear this fellow in the <qex>cellarage</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Chare for storage in a cellar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cellarer</ent>⟦br⟧
